'''Peru''' is a town in [[Dunn County, Wisconsin|Dunn County]], [[Wisconsin]], [[United States]]. The population was 247 at the 2000 census. The unincorporated communities of [[Meridean, Wisconsin|Meridean]] and [[Red Cedar, Wisconsin|Red Cedar]] are located in the town. The ghost town of [[Old Tyrone, Wisconsin|Old Tyrone]] was also located in the town.

==Geography==
According to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the town has a total area of 19.6&nbsp;square miles (50.8&nbsp;km<U+00B2>), of which, 18.7&nbsp;square miles (48.5&nbsp;km<U+00B2>) of it is land and 0.9&nbsp;square miles (2.3&nbsp;km<U+00B2>) of it (4.49%) is water.

==Demographics==
{{USCensusPop
|1990= 203
|2000= 247
|2010= 242
|estimate=243
|estyear=2012
}}
As of the [[census]]{{GR|2}} of 2000, there were 247 people, 83 households, and 68 families residing in the town. The [[population density]] was 13.2 people per square mile (5.1/km<U+00B2>). There were 86 housing units at an average density of 4.6 per square mile (1.8/km<U+00B2>). The racial makeup of the town was 93.52% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.81% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 4.05% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.40% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 1.21% from two or more races.

There were 83 households out of which 43.4% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 73.5% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 4.8% had a female householder with no husband present, and 16.9% were non-families. 14.5% of all households were made up of individuals and 6.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.98 and the average family size was 3.30.

In the town the population was spread out with 32.4% under the age of 18, 8.5% from 18 to 24, 25.9% from 25 to 44, 21.5% from 45 to 64, and 11.7% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 34 years. For every 100 females there were 111.1 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 108.8 males.

The median income for a household in the town was $34,375, and the median income for a family was $50,625. Males had a median income of $29,286 versus $16,875 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $14,774. About 8.2% of families and 10.8% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 14.1% of those under the age of eighteen and 6.1% of those sixty five or over.

